@startuml state-app-lifecycle
title App Shell — PWA Lifecycle State Diagram

[*] --> Loading : App opened

Loading --> Online : Network available,\nservice worker registered

Online --> Offline : Network lost
Offline --> Online : Network restored

state Online {
  [*] --> Active
  Active --> BackgroundSync : App backgrounded
  BackgroundSync --> Active : App foregrounded
  Active --> UpdateAvailable : New SW version detected
  UpdateAvailable --> Updating : User accepts update\nor auto-update
  Updating --> Active : SW activated,\npage reloaded
}

state Offline {
  [*] --> CachedContent : Serving from\nservice worker cache
  CachedContent --> LimitedMode : Requested content\nnot cached
  LimitedMode --> CachedContent : Navigate to\ncached content
}

note right of Offline
  OfflineIndicator banner shown.
  Only cached content and
  previously downloaded media
  are available.
end note

note right of UpdateAvailable
  User sees prompt:
  "A new version is available.
  Tap to update."
end note

note left of Loading
  Splash screen shown.
  SW registration and
  cache check in progress.
end note

@enduml
